This paper describes the architecture of a digital object repository designed for ingesting, storing, and accessing a vast collection of digital objects. The paper discusses the use of XML-based formats, ingestion processes, and front-ends for requesting and disseminating digital objects. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Databases (cs.DB), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
